HEADWORD: Scorching
<hw>Scorch"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Burning; parching or
shriveling with heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>sufficiently hot to cause scorching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Scorch"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Scorch"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Score</ent>⟦br⟧
